{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HShLz8SeJMTXYnnvk5Ln6B","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTP 200 and exit code 0. HTTPS is fully restored.\n\n**Summary of what happened and what was fixed:**\n\n**Root cause:** The TLS secret `expired-tls-secret` referenced by the `demo-ingress` Ingress resource had been deleted from the cluster, causing the nginx ingress controller to have no certificate to serve for `demo.example.com`.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Identified the correct CA (`CN=Test CA`, created Jul 1 2026) by extracting its cert from the curl-test pod's `/tmp/tls/ca.crt` and matching it to `/tmp/test-ca.key` on the host.\n2. Generated a new RSA 2048 private key and CSR for `demo.example.com` with the proper SAN extension.\n3. Signed it with the Test CA, creating a valid cert (valid until Jun 30 2028).\n4. Recreated the `expired-tls-secret` with `kubectl create secret tls`.\n\nThe nginx ingress controller picked up the new secret and HTTPS now validates correctly with `SSL certificate verify ok` and returns `hello` (HTTP 200)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":351,"cache_read_input_tokens":50651,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":351},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd22eb05-06ce-430c-a239-b717975d7f4d","uuid":"238f2146-d1d8-45f3-afa8-c370d280fdca","request_id":"req_011CcanGwyxHTEFnRTNmRhKi"}
